## Data Handling Notice

This software facilitates the transmission of pull request content (code diffs
and metadata) to third-party artificial intelligence service providers chosen
and configured solely by the user. By using this software, you acknowledge and
agree that:

1. **User responsibility.** You are solely responsible for ensuring that any
   transmission of code, data, or metadata to a third-party AI provider
   complies with your applicable laws and regulations (including but not limited
   to data protection and privacy law), your intellectual property rights and
   obligations, any contractual commitments you hold with third parties, and the
   terms of service and acceptable use policies of your chosen AI provider.

2. **No warranty regarding third parties.** The authors and copyright holders
   make no representation or warranty, express or implied, regarding the
   security, privacy practices, data retention policies, legal compliance, or
   fitness for any particular purpose of any third-party AI service. You are
   solely responsible for reviewing and accepting the data handling and privacy
   policies of any AI provider you configure.

3. **No liability for transmitted content.** The authors and copyright holders
   accept no liability of any kind arising from the content transmitted to, the
   processing of that content by, or any actions taken by, third-party AI
   providers as a result of your use of this software.

4. **Security decisions are yours.** The built-in sensitive data scan is
   provided as a best-effort automated check. It does not constitute a guarantee
   that no sensitive data will be transmitted. You remain responsible for
   reviewing what you allow this software to transmit on your behalf.
